The paper deals with blind image deblurring, which is a problem in computer vision and image processing. The proposed method involves using a Gaussian mixture model to learn a class-adapted prior, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of machine learning techniques to learn the prior also suggests that the paper could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves signal processing techniques to handle the ill-posed inverse problem, which suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories.
